Popular actress Rita Dominic has offered a probable diagnosis for individuals who continuously seek validation from others. According to her, such people are fueled by insecurity to seek validation from others.   Singer R. Kelly gets 30-year jail term for sex crimes     Laycon, Oxlade, Praiz become Recording Academy members     Kizz Daniel’s ‘Buga’ amasses 10 million YouTube…   She explained the lack of confidence in one or judgment would always make a person chase after other people’s approval before acting on anything. The 46-year-old newly wedded movie star said people should rather make decisions and take actions rather than wait for others’ opinions. “The constant need to be validated by others is a sign of insecurity. Just do you, simple,” she wrote.